    "minides": "Lamborghini's first hybrid V12 — the Aventador's spiritual successor — pairing an 825 CV naturally-aspirated 6.5L V12 with three electric motors for 1015 CV combined and a silent 10 km EV-only city mode.",
    "description": "The Lamborghini Revuelto launched in India in late 2023 as the direct successor to the Aventador and Lamborghini's first-ever series-production plug-in hybrid. Unveiled globally on 29 March 2023, it pairs a brand-new naturally-aspirated 6.5L V12 (825 CV on its own) with three electric motors — two front-axle motors for torque-vectoring AWD and one integrated into the new 8-speed dual-clutch transmission — for a combined 1015 CV (1001 bhp) and 807 Nm. The carbon-fibre monocoque 'Monofuselage' chassis is dramatically lighter and stiffer than the Aventador's, with a fully exposed V12 visible through the rear buttresses. A 3.8 kWh battery enables up to 10 km of silent, pure-EV 'Città' driving. The Revuelto is sold as a single, fully-loaded variant in India, with deep Ad Personam customisation available on paint, wheels, and interior trim — including bespoke one-off 'Opera Unica' commissions."
  },
